[normal]2.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]It is important that transport planning is integrated with land use planning so that transport facilities can be developed to meet future needs at the outset. 
[normal]In May 2012 we set out 
[normal]plans for 
[normal]route based strategies (RBS
[normal]s
[normal])
[normal] 
[normal]to 
[normal]identify 
[normal]the management and enhancement 
[normal]needs 
[normal]of our road network
[normal],
[normal] tak
[normal]ing
[normal] account of local needs and interests
[normal], including
[normal] local authorities, Local Enterprise Partnerships, motorists’ organis
[normal]ations, environmental groups and others
[normal].
[normal]2.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Recent H
[normal]A schemes already include successful links with local transport –
[normal]for example 
[normal]new improvements to the A453 will connect directly to park and ride facilities on the Nottingham Express Transit extension. 
[normal]Over t
[normal]he next two years RBS
[normal]s
[normal] will cover all of the network and 
[normal]help identify where these synergies exist
[normal], and will form a key part of the evidence that will inform the first Roads Investment Strategy
[normal]. 
[normal]This may include identifying
[normal] cases where the best way to addr
[normal]ess capacity issues on the 
[normal]SRN
[normal] will be to do something
[normal] on other networks.
[normal] 
[normal]More broadly, w
[normal]e will also seek to 
[normal]align road 
[normal]and
[normal] 
[normal]rail investment strategies 
[normal]from 2017. 
[normal]2.3.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]We should not be looking to choose between investing in roads and investing in rail if we want to remain internationally competitive. 
[normal]That is why they Government has committed to significant, complementary investments in both our road and rail networks.
[normal] T
[normal]r
[normal]ansformative projects such as HS2 and Crossrail are investments in our national economic success. It is important that these networks serve to complement one another to enhance the 
[normal]UK
[normal]’s connectivity. Subject to consultation, the proposed HS2 stations at Bi
[normal]rmingham International, 
[normal]Manchester
[normal] 
[normal]Airport
[normal], East Midlands and
[normal] 
[normal]Sheffield
