[normal]&#xa0;[bold]3.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The N
[normal]ational 
[normal]T
[normal]ransport 
[normal]M
[normal]odel (NTM)
[normal] is designed to forecast long-term trends (currently 2010 to 2040 in five year intervals) based on:
[normal]3.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The three key drivers for road traffic are population, income and the costs
[normal] of road transport
[normal]. Between 2010-2040 the population in 
[normal]England
[normal] is expected to rise by 20%, GDP 
[normal]per capita is projected to 
[normal]rise by 57% and the fuel cost of driving is projected to fall by 28%. By 2040 
[normal]SRN
[normal] traffic is forecast 
[normal](in the central case) 
[normal]to be 46% higher than in 2010, implying an increase in congestion (measured
[normal] 
[normal]as lost time) of about 114%.
[normal]3.3.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]B
[normal]ackcasting exercise
[normal]s, which 
[normal]input past economic and demographic drivers into the NTM accurately 
[normal]support projections of
[normal] actual traffic growth on all roads in 
[normal]England
[normal], 
[normal]and 
[normal]give us confidence in our forecast
[normal]s
[normal], 
[normal]though we acknowledge that our model tends to 
[normal]ov
[normal]erestimate traffic in urban areas (e.g. 
[normal]London
[normal]) and underestimate traffic in rural areas
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]We continually work to update and improve our modelling and understanding on what and why something is happening and the impact on the future.
[normal]3.4.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]However, u
[normal]ncertainty is inherently part of forecasting and predicting future behaviour and trends. 
[normal]T
[normal]raffic trends and outcomes depend on a large number of variables, economic (
[normal]GDP
[normal], oil prices) and behavioural (people preferences, trends and social habits). 
[normal]Forecasts
[normal] must be interpreted as best estimates given 
[normal]the 
[normal]current state of
[normal] 
[normal]information and assumptions. We seek
[normal] to 
[normal]reflect
[normal] this uncertainty by using 
[normal]scenario analysis and 
[normal]sensitivity analysis to understand 
[normal]the 
[normal]impact
[normal] of different assumptions
[normal] and 
[normal]a range of potentia
[normal]l alternative outcome
[normal]s
[normal]. 
[normal]3.5.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]We are exploring any changing patterns in the demand to travel, 
[normal]using the latest National Travel Survey (NTS) data
