[normal]&#xa0;[bold]5.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The 
[normal]G
[normal]overnment is committed to investing in our national road infrastructure to improve capacity, reduce conges
[normal]tion and enhance connectivity across the country. 
[normal]In 
[normal]Investing in Britain’s Future
[normal], the Government outlined a dramatic increase in the level of public investment in infrastructure of all kinds, including roads. 
[normal]This will fund the biggest-ever upgrade of our existing network. 
[normal]5.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]In delivering this investment, we will consider the ways in which the private sector can best help speed delivery and drive efficiency.
[normal]  
[normal]5.3.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]We continue to rule out tolls as a mechanism to fund
[normal] existing roads. However
[normal],
[normal] t
[normal]here will be cases where the combination of the significant expense of the scheme and the distribution of the benefits means that it is fair that users meet some of the costs of the scheme, rather than general taxpayers. This wou
[normal]ld be in very limited circumstances where schemes deliver new roads or transform an existing road into an entirely new route beyond all recognition and there is a strong economic and commercial case for a contribution from tolling.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] 
